anms.examples.stocks.text1: The grammarian plays an important role in helping all club members improve their grammar and vocabulary. As grammarian you
anms.examples.stocks.text2: Introduce new words to meeting participants and monitor language and grammar usage
anms.examples.stocks.text3: The purpose of the Ah-Counter is to note any overused words or filler sounds used as a crutch by anyone who speaks during the meeting. Words may be inappropriate interjections, such as and, well, but, so and you know. Sounds may be ah, um or er. As Ah-Counter you
anms.examples.stocks.text4: In the Ah-Counter’s log, record overlong pauses, overused words and filler sounds relied upon too often by all speakers. Examples include: and, but, so, you know, ah, um.

anms.examples.todos.text9: Contact Speakers, General Evaluator and Table Topics Master at least 3 days before the meeting to discuss the theme and obtain the title of each speech. Ask them a question related to your theme that you can tie into your introduction and ask them how they want to be introduced.
